{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "05", "m": "04", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "16", "M": "22", "S": "59"}}, "news": [{"title": "MIDC invites tender for 338-acre slum overhaul in Thane-Belapur", "para": "MIDC has launched one of the Mumbai Metropolitan Region's largest slum rehabilitation projects, covering 338 acres along the Thane-Belapur industrial belt. The initiative aims to redevelop nearly 35,800 slum structures, transforming the area into a mixed-use zone. Developers must be capable of rehabilitating over 1,900 families, with the project divided into three packages for simultaneous execution.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/infrastructure/midc-launches-major-slum-rehabilitation-project-in-thane-belapur/130042534?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-23182/130042534.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "infrastructure"}, {"title": "Property registrations in Gujarat drop to 1,610 in FY26", "para": "Gujarat's real estate sector has seen new project registrations drop to their lowest point since FY 2021, with 1,610 registrations. This slowdown follows four years of strong post-pandemic demand, attributed to market saturation and developer caution. However, an uptick is anticipated in FY 2027, especially with Ahmedabad hosting the Commonwealth Games 2030.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/residential/gujarat-property-registrations-plummet-to-lowest-since-fy-2021/130042421?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-728427/130042421.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "residential"}, {"title": "Delhi govt plans slum rehabilitation policy with shopping complexes, e-rickshaw charging", "para": "The Delhi government is preparing a new policy to provide modern facilities like shopping complexes and e-rickshaw charging points to slum dwellers. The policy also plans to extend the eligibility cut-off date for permanent housing by ten years, making more residents eligible. This initiative aims to improve living conditions and housing access for those in the city's numerous slum clusters.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/infrastructure/delhi-government-unveils-ambitious-slum-rehabilitation-policy-with-modern-amenities/130042306?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-269562/130042306.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "infrastructure"}]}